{
  "texts": [
    "For example, according to a seminal review paper [1] \"in the 1980s there were at least 68 (AI) systems in research, 38 in development, nine in field test and 14 in production use\".",
    "Both the algorithmic developments reported in that paper and broader developments in so-called Expert Systems [2] indicated AI was being extensively explored.",
    "Twenty years later, collaborator Vlad Marik and I reported a wide range of AI applications under development [3] and in between times there have been a vast number of academic works exploring the role of AI but relatively modest industrial take up of the technology.",
    "So what has been holding AI in industry up, what is happening now and why is it different?We examine this in the light of one of the most influential developments in the industrial digital systems space-the strategic initiative Industrie 4.0 which emerged in Germany in the early 2010s [4].",
    "Industrie 4.0 emerged as part of the excitement around digitalization and became a de facto name for the 4th Industrial Revolution."
  ]
}